01

Fewer than 100 new deaths

On the 17th, January twenty-four, the sky was still clear.

On the 17th, there were 1886 new confirmed cases, 1097 new severe cases, 98 new deaths (93 in Hubei, 3 in Henan, 1 in Hebei and 1 in Hunan) , and 105 new deaths on the 16th.

As of July 17, there were 58,016 confirmed cases (11,741 severe cases) , 12,552 cured cases (7 cases of Beijing Nuclear Proliferation) , 1,868 dead cases and 6,242 suspected cases.

A total of 1,807 new cases were confirmed in Hubei (1600 in Wuhan) on July 17, and 1,933 in Wuhan on June 16. There were 93 new deaths (72 in Wuhan and 76 in Wuhan on the 16th) . There were 50338 confirmed cases (37152 in Wuhan) , including 10970 severe cases (9222 in Wuhan) .

There were 1789 cumulative deaths (1381 in Wuhan) and 59989 confirmed cases (42752 in Wuhan) .

There were 79 newly confirmed cases in China except Hubei Province, which decreased for the 14th consecutive day. The data of the previous days were 890(3 days) , 731(4 days) , 707(5 days) , 696(6 days) , 558(7 days) , 509(8 days) , 444(9 days) , 381(10 days) , 377(11 days) , 312(12 days) , 267(13 days) , 221(14 days) , 166(15 days) and 115(16 days) .

Behind these figures are the results of national support for Hubei.

More than 30,000 medical personnel, mainly from smoking, infection and severe illness, were recruited by the COVID-19, the State Council's joint prevention and Control Mechanism said at a news conference on pneumonia in Beijing on Wednesday, there are 11,000 critical care professionals in charge of critical care. The 11,000 critical care workers represent nearly 10 percent of the nation's critical care workforce.

02

The national two sessions will be postponed

The 13th Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, at its forty-seven th meeting of chairmen on the 17th, decided that, a Standing Committee of the National People's Congress meeting on February 24th will consider a draft decision to postpone the third session of the 13th National People's Congress.

The thirty-three previous meetings of the chairmen of the 13th National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) had considered matters relating to the postponement of the third session of the 13th National Committee of the CPPCC and the 10th session of the Standing Committee.

At present, the epidemic situation is still very grim, epidemic prevention and control work to the most difficult key stage. The postponement of the two sessions of the National People's Congress is also aimed at fulfilling the requirement that the safety of the people's lives and their health should be given top priority.

The constitution and relevant laws and regulations do not specify the specific time of the annual national two sessions.

The early sessions of the National People's Congress and the plenary sessions of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference were held at Irregular Times. In 1959, the National People's Congress (NPC) and the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) began to "loop open" in a similar time period. In 1975, when the National People's Congress met and the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) did not meet, the term "two sessions" came into being.

Since 1985, the holding time of the national two sessions has been basically stable in March every year, and gradually moved from late March to early March (among which the Fifth Session of the Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference opened on February 27,1997) . Since 1998, the National People's Congress (NPC) and the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) have been held on March 5 and 3 respectively.

I didn't change from 2003 to 2012, when I was in the 10th and 11th member of the National People's Congress.

On the 17th, the Central Working Leading Group to deal with the epidemic of new pneumonia held a meeting. There are three things we're particularly interested in. It's all important stuff.

First, Wuhan and Hubei provinces should continue to step up screening efforts to expand the supply of beds.

Second, the state in accordance with the need to send additional medical support.

The third is to ensure that Wuhan and Hubei Prevention and control materials and critical treatment equipment.

On the afternoon of the 17th, the Joint Defense and Joint Control Mechanism of the State Council held a press conference.

According to Sun Yanrong, deputy director of the Biological Center of the Ministry of Science and technology, chloroquine phosphate is effective in treating new coronary pneumonia.

Qingfei Paidu decoction has good clinical efficacy and therapeutic prospect, said Li Yu, director of the State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine.

The good medicine has finally arrived.

The Ministry of Civil Affairs issued the "urgent notice of the General Office of the Ministry of Civil Affairs on further strengthening the relief and management agencies for vagrants and beggars with no means of livelihood and their target COVID-19 for the prevention and control of the epidemic of pneumonia, " Issued the "homeless beggars without means of Livelihood Relief Management Agency new pneumonia epidemic prevention and control guidelines. ".

I'm particularly interested in the news.

February 7, I put forward the "civil affairs departments pay attention to the "Nikko Clan" proposal:

At present, in addition to patients, medical staff, community cadres, but also pay attention to low-income, no income of the homeless.

Read an article, all over the "closure of the city" since some very low-income people how to do? For example, usually by begging for a living, now there are no pedestrians on the road. Junkman, Junkyard's closed. Where's breakfast today?

On a deserted street recently, I saw a man, without a mask, unkempt hair, unshaven beard, a small four-wheel cart full of mineral water bottles, in a helpless first go. Where can I collect his junk?

I call these people the solariums. That's money, that's money, that's money. He worked as a rag-picker and day-laborer to meet his daily expenses. Used to be able to scrape by. And now there's nothing to be done.

It is suggested that civil affairs departments at all levels should pay attention to and settle down.

It's really taken care of now.

On the 14th, the State New Office of the People's Republic of China issued an update on the progress of the epidemic prevention and control, especially the care for medical personnel initiative. It was stated that medical care and related staff died of new crown pneumonia or of new crown pneumonia as a result of performing their duties, clearly identified as industrial injury, according to the law to enjoy industrial injury insurance treatment.

This is obviously not enough. Netizens want to be able to designate martyrs.

Sure enough, the Department of Veterans Affairs and the Department of Political Work of the Central Military Commission jointly issued the notice on properly doing a good job in commending the martyrs who lost their lives in the prevention and control of the new pneumonia epidemic, and those who meet the criteria for martyrs'assessment (approval) , be Rated (approved) as a martyr.

On the afternoon of July 17, Zhong Nanshan said his team had developed a mathematical model that took into account two variables -- strong state intervention and the peak return of migrant workers after Chinese new year -- that would alter the natural course of the disease. According to the model, the number of cases in the country is expected to peak in mid-to-late February, but that does not mean that it will drop immediately after the peak. However, the epidemic is likely to return with the return of migrant workers again a new peak.

The warning is justified.

Zhong Nanshan said Wuhan still has a high morbidity and mortality rate, accounting for 80 percent of the country's total number of patients and more than 95 percent of the country's mortality rate.

The impact of new coronary pneumonia on the economy, various experts have put forward views.

Liu Shijin, deputy director of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and former deputy director of the Development Research Center of the State Council, said that the Bozhi Macro Forum online symposium hosted by the China Development Research Foundation was held through an online platform on Thursday, the epidemic situation of China's economic and social development in the deep-seated contradictions to provide a rare opportunity for reflection, correction, reform.

Efforts should be made to bring the epidemic under control by the end of February, involving only industry, construction and agriculture. The overall situation of the national economy will not be broken.

If it extends beyond March, the effect will be long-term productivity, with many businesses failing to execute contracts, pay wages, and cash flow, forcing them to close. That's when it hurts.

So you can't have an unexpected short-term shock (Black Swan) turn into a medium-or even long-term shock.

Research published by the Beijing University of International Business and Economics supports this view. Among the participating enterprises, 69.23% of the cash flow can be maintained for more than three months, and 43.83% can be maintained for more than half a year. If the outbreak is not effectively contained within three months, companies will face the risk of bankruptcy.

What is the centralized grid-type large-scale investigation?

On the 17th, the COVID-19 of Hubei Province issued a notice on matters related to the investigation and verification of fever patients, which has been carried out since January 20, fever patients in various medical institutions, people who buy antipyretic and antitussive drugs through physical pharmacies or order them on the Internet, grasp the above-mentioned personnel to see a doctor or purchase time, name, citizenship number, current address, contact telephone information, and organize home verification, follow-up testing, isolation and treatment and other work.

It's a way of backtracking.

In Wuhan, they entered a three-day siege period.

From the 17th, the city mobilization, began to carry out a 3-day centralized dragnet-type investigation. In all sorts of ways.

Count the windows. On the evening of the 16th, the community grid all went down to the building, door-to-door building residents light up the situation, compared with the previous survey data, missing fill.

Come to my door. "Hello, how many people are at home now? " "How is your family? " "What's the temperature today? " ... Early on the morning of the 17th, the Taipei Street community in Taoyuan, Jiang'an District, was divided by a grid, one Grid member, One Community Cadre, one sinking cadre and one volunteer were assigned to each grid. A grid-based search was carried out, door-to-door inquiries were made, and key inquiries were made regarding the newly added household list.

Check the meter. There's a difference between a house that's occupied and a house that's not.

Asked the machine. Residents of Dexin, Jiufeng street in the Donghu New Technology Development Zone district, have been followed up by AI voice visits from the Donghu New Technology Development Zone. This conversation, over the telephone line, real-time transmission to the system back-office centre of the Donghu New Technology Development Zone, located three kilometres away, is converted into a written record on a computer.

The community staff through the log-in account, check the results of external feedback data, found in the dialogue there is "thermometer broken" this key information, the staff quickly take the thermometer home check.

The system can make 900 calls at a time. For example, on the 16th day, 172616 people were called in 32 communities on Kanto Street, and 121059 people were successfully answered, with a connection rate of 70.1% ; 154128 person-times were informed by short message; 69 residents with fever and 331 with cough weakness were screened out.

Robots are better than people. Without such a system, the simplest solution is to make a phone call and record it on a form.

Smart Platform. "Intelligent grass-roots social governance comprehensive support platform" also has 1315 households in the Guanggu Buddha Ridge B community running. With the help of facial recognition cameras, outsiders can not enter the community through the entrances and exits.

In a gated community, if you're out on the street, you're welcome.

At about 18 pm on the 16th, Zou (a 44-year-old man who lives in a community on Hongshan District's Happy Avenue) refused to cooperate with the management of the closure of the community, saying that the provincial and municipal community closed management of the relevant regulations against the law, to drive into the community, and abuse, pushing and shoving the police on duty. According to the law, the Public Security Bureau detained him for 10 days and fined him 500 yuan.

At around 10:00 am on the 17th, when the police and community cadres of the castle peak public security sub-bureau advised a man to wear a mask near the Badajiayuan community, the man refused to cooperate and repeatedly provoked the police, threatening to "wear handcuffs before wearing a mask" , causing a crowd of nearby residents to watch. Repeated persuasion of the police is invalid, according to law, the implementation of compulsory summons, and administrative detention for five days. I saw this video. The man is very rude.

Completely closed to the community, buying food naturally became a big problem. And all kinds of ways to do it. For example, you need a pass to buy food. Haven't heard of it.

New Hanyang District Crown Pneumonia Control Headquarters issued headquarters order No. 46 on the use of resident passes in major supermarkets, stipulating that from this day on, all shoppers entering supermarkets, a resident pass issued by the office of the new Hanyang District pneumonia control and Prevention Headquarters is required. Residents who do not hold the resident pass are not allowed to enter the supermarket (Business Hours: 10:00 am-17:00 am) . In case of violation, the epidemic prevention and control work in accordance with the relevant requirements of the wartime state, in accordance with the rules and regulations.

This is the first I've heard of it. Not For long, of course. Passes aren't very clean.

Some supermarkets don't even serve individual customers.

From the 17th, all large and medium-sized supermarkets and commercial outlets in Qingshan district will only accept group purchase customers, and will no longer sell daily necessities to individuals.

From the 17th, Wuchang District Shangchao only accept group purchase customers. If residents have shopping needs, they can contact the community where they live and take part in community group shopping. By the chain supermarket as the main vegetable distributor, responsible for the entire area of 14 streets and communities for the full coverage of distribution.

Promotion and love

Hubei issued "measures to further care for and inspire the first-line medical personnel in the prevention and control of the new pneumonia epidemic" , proposing that the children of the first-line medical personnel will be enrolled in kindergartens in the autumn of 2020, priority will be given to children enrolled in public welfare and inclusive kindergartens in their districts; those who will be enrolled in primary schools or junior middle schools in the fall of 2020 will be coordinated by the education administration departments of the counties, cities and districts where their household registration is located, subject to the availability of a degree, in accordance with the principle of proximity, priority is given to the admission of relatively high-quality schools; for those who take the secondary school entrance examination in 2020, the municipality or prefecture concerned may take the secondary school entrance examination after an increase of 10 points on the basis of their total admission score.

In 2020, the first-line medical personnel's children to participate in the General College Entrance Examination for admission to provincial colleges and universities, according to the candidates'wishes in the same batch of priority adjustment of professional; Arrangements for some of the province's high-quality vocational colleges to recruit first-line medical staff children, the implementation of a separate plan.

Regarding the performance of medical personnel in epidemic prevention and control work as an important basis for personnel evaluation and personnel management, and giving preference to medical personnel who have made contributions in the evaluation of their professional titles, the selection of talent projects and the employment of posts in public institutions, give priority to recommendation and promotion.

05

Moving stories make people cry

These days, there is a sad story circulating on Wechat.

Chang Kai, director and director of the Hubei Film Studio, died within 17 days, along with his parents and sister, who were infected with new-crown pneumonia. Chang Kai and his sister died on the same day. His parents died on the 27th of last month and the 2nd of this month respectively. Chang Kai's parents are both professors at Tongji Hospital in Wuhan, Hubei Province. Hundreds of millions of netizens cheer on Chang Kai's wife, who is still in hospital, and wish her a speedy recovery.

"We're just stuck at home, " one netizen wrote. "Some of us are stuck in 2020 forever. ".

This is perhaps the most heart-wrenching news of the new pneumonia of 2020.

And in the battle against the new crown pneumonia in Wuhan, there are also some touching stories that make people cry.

On the 17th, 358 new pneumonia patients admitted to the Provincial Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine received a "care package" of daily necessities from the hospital, there are toilet paper, toothbrush, toothpaste, towels, Shampoo, shower gel, laundry detergent and Feminine hygiene, many patients for this warm heart service like.

Owners are generally against overcharging property. At this time in Hankou, 107 owners of a residential area, but to the property "bonus. ".

In the aftermath of the outbreak, the property has become more focused on its work. Property co-owners through a variety of purchase mode —— Vegetables through train, contact co-operative direct supply vegetables, so that this community 2153 households, nearly 10,000 residents to eat vegetables, more a smooth security.

Property staff due diligence, close to the people, but also let the owners treat each other wholeheartedly.

Founder, enthusiastic owner Feng Jianhua told reporters that many owners "private letter" him, please him to launch the collection, "can not only for the property like, to point to the real. ".

So he wrote a note to the owners@all:

"behind our well-being, there are always people who carry the weight for us! We Jinhe neighbors of the comfort, is all the property comrades are willing to work hard, she Xiaojia for everyone! Spring Festival holidays, and the epidemic, the natural reduction of the property staff, now can top up the people is hard-pressed. Whether it is security or cleaning aunt, see the new year since the post is always these people, I always feel some pain. Here, I would like to suggest: All our neighbors donate some money (how much is a gesture) to the property comrades to do overtime or meal. It's not easy for them!"

On the 12th, less than 12 hours later, donations had reached 59,646 yuan. In the end, the couple added 354 yuan to 15 one-unit buildings, making up 60,000 yuan.

Interestingly, the property company did not include the US, made a detailed allocation table is impressive. This can be written into the future of social governance and harmonious society in the teaching plan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Since the outbreak, the Han-tibetan Cultural Exchange Center, which is located next to the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center, has donated 40,000 masks to the Wuhan Tibet Middle School, the Hubei Hospital for integrated traditional and Western medicine, the Kong Hon Traffic Police Brigade, relevant streets and communities, and provided breakfast, lunch and dinner for more than 400 medical staff at Kong Hon's "Shelter Hospital" .

This restaurant, which I have been to several times, is small in size and serves three meals for more than 400 people.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At the Wakanda coffee shop on Guanggu Pedestrian Street, seven employees are busy, surrounded by cardboard boxes and coffee bags.

The coffee shop has a clientele -- medical staff at the Hubei Provincial Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine -- including heavy coffee drinkers who drink at least one cup a day and a cup of pick me up after work. Coffee Shop's closed. What are they drinking? The boss was concerned.

As a result, starting from January 26, the coffee shop temporarily set up a seven-person team, Hubei Provincial Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine Guanggu Park and Huayuanshan Hospital area to provide 500 cups of coffee free of charge every day.

Many netizens found the store through the take-out APP and expressed their support for the goodwill and the "epidemic" of the war through the "cloud payment" approach. In just a few days, the total bill has reached more than 1.2 million yuan.

"We were shocked when we found the money in the background. We were just doing what we thought we should do. We were very moved by the support behind us, " the boss said.

"You watch over them, we watch over you. " "thank you for giving the little people a chance to support the front line in the context of the war epidemic. " "when the epidemic is over and the spring flowers are blooming and the cherry blossoms are blooming, be sure to come to the shop for coffee, it will taste delicious! " Netizens said, it inspires everyone.

As a token of their support, our friends at the Coffee Shop keep a handwritten message on each cup of coffee, along with the name of the person who donated the coffee.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It reminds me of a snack bar.

On April 12,2013, Weibo user Chen Li launched the@ready-to-eat fast food campaign on Weibo, advocating the concept of "rich and loving, poor and helpful, ready-to-use public welfare, and help each other with dignity. ". Similar to the European concept of "standby coffee" .

The social significance of the "micro-charity" of ready-to-eat fast food is twofold: On the one hand, it helps the needy and needy by providing them with free help, while at the same time providing them with real help, they also feel the warmth and respect from the community; on the other hand, it can spread the power of public welfare in a wider scope, the warmth of charity, can touch the good in everyone's heart.

After the outbreak, every restaurant is expected to have a door, has been paid for food, waiting for those in need of selection.
